commit.message:
Catch error for non-standard cursor

Adwaita icon theme does not contain `exchange` legacy X11 cursor
so attempting to mask HCY wheel on GNOME will cause a crash:

    Gdk-Message: Unable to load exchange from the cursor theme
    TypeError: constructor returned NULL

Let’s catch the error like in https://github.com/mypaint/mypaint/commit/cf14342d9ad609ffd92eef965450281f8ddb3fc1
and fall back to default cursor when not present.

Modernize cursor creation

- `Gdk.Cursor.new` is deprecated in favour of `new_for_display`
  but `new_from_name` is actually preferred these days
  since it uses name from xdg cursor-spec draft:
  https://docs.gtk.org/gdk3/ctor.Cursor.new.html
  https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Specifications/cursor-spec/
- `arrow` refers to right-pointing diagonal arrow according to image in
  https://docs.gtk.org/gdk3/enum.CursorType.html
  But in Adwaita, as well as our pixmaps, it is just a regular
  left-pointing arrow so let’s change it to default.
- In the standard `*_corner`/`*_side` cursors are `resize`,
  `fleur` is called `move`, and `wait` is `watch`.
- `plus` and `exchange` no not have standard equivalents.

Use standard cursor name

Adwaita, the resident icon theme on GNOME removed the legacy X11 `circle` cursor:
https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/adwaita-icon-theme/-/commit/fb133a3989ee155c24201e30bab7dbc1c7c843fd

As a result, MyPaint would break when opening a file on GNOME systems.

Let’s use the equivalent `not-allowed` cursor from the XDG cursor-spec draft:
https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Specifications/cursor-spec/

The circle cursor that was removed from Adwaita is in the fourth row, second column here:
https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/adwaita-icon-theme/-/blob/4d082e44e8361ca32360bb5b865be98a784ef4db/src/cursors/adwaita.svg
Here is the list of cursor constants supported by GDK 3 with images – it includes legacy X11 cursors:
https://docs.gtk.org/gdk3/enum.CursorType.html
Here is the list of cursor names – only contains standard ones:
https://docs.gtk.org/gdk3/ctor.Cursor.new_from_name.html

Fixes: https://github.com/mypaint/mypaint/issues/1209
